UPDPKGSUMS(8)                                                                              Pacman-contrib Manual                                                                             UPDPKGSUMS(8)

NAME
       updpkgsums - update checksums of a PKGBUILD file

SYNOPSIS
       updpkgsums [options] [build file]

DESCRIPTION
       updpkgsums will perform an in place update of the checksums in the path specified by [build file], defaulting to PKGBUILD in the current working directory.

OPTIONS
       -h, --help
           Display syntax and command-line options.

       -m, --nocolor
           Do not colorize output.

       -V, --version
           Display version information.

SEE ALSO
       makepkg(8), pkgbuild(5)

BUGS
       Bugs? You must be kidding; there are no bugs in this software. But if we happen to be wrong, file an issue with as much detail as possible at
       https://gitlab.archlinux.org/pacman/pacman-contrib/-/issues/new.

